# Version bumps (semver)

When a change is user-visible or affects compatibility, bump the **app version** using [semver](https://semver.org/): **patch** (fixes), **minor** (backward-compatible features or behavior additions), **major** (breaking changes, incompatible UX/API, or removals users rely on).

**Always keep these files on the same version** (replace `X.Y.Z` everywhere in one edit, then refresh lockfiles):

| File | Notes |
|------|--------|
| `package.json` | `"version"` |
| `package-lock.json` | Root `"version"` and `packages[""].version` — run `npm install` after editing `package.json` to sync reliably |
| `src-tauri/Cargo.toml` | `[package].version` |
| `src-tauri/Cargo.lock` | `[[package]]` entry for `name = "solitaire"` |
| `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json` | `"version"` (Tauri bundle / updater metadata) |

Do not bump only one file. After edits, run `npm install` from the repo root if `package-lock.json` was not updated by hand; run `cargo build` or `cargo check` in `src-tauri` if `Cargo.lock` needs to refresh.

GitHub Releases use tags like `vX.Y.Z`; the tag should match the app version.
